AMEND S e n ate Bill No. 2053 House Bill No. 1827*
by deleting all language after the enacting clause and substituting:
SECTION 1. Tennessee Code Annotated, Title 7, Chapter 51, is amended by adding
the following as a new part:
7-51-2801. Purpose and intent.
(a) The general assembly finds that certain proposed quarries and digital asset
mining facilities can create substantial impacts on surrounding communities when they
are developed without sufficient planning, engineering, or operational safeguards. The
purpose of this act is not to prohibit quarrying or digital asset mining, nor to hinder
responsible commercial operators, but to ensure that these facilities are sited and
developed only when the applicant provides clear, credible, and professionally prepared
proof that the operation can be conducted safely and responsibly.
(b) With respect to nuisance quarries, the general assembly recognizes that
small quarry sites located in close proximity to existing residential dwellings present
heightened risks relating to noise, dust, vibration, truck traffic, groundwater disturbance,
and overall community compatibility. This part is intended to ensure that only quarry
operators capable of demonstrating modern standards of safety, environmental
compliance, and financial responsibility may develop close-proximity, small-footprint
quarry sites.
(c) With respect to digital asset mining facilities, the general assembly
recognizes that large-scale, high-density data mining and blockchain operations can
impose material impacts on local communities, including very high electrical demand,
HA0785
